You can forget your Ronaldinhos and David Beckhams - Aaron Ramsey has revealed that his childhood hero was none other than former Cardiff and Wigan midfielder Graham Kavanagh.

Kavanagh spent four years at Cardiff between 2001 and 2005 while a young Ramsey was working his way through their academy before making his debut in 2006.

The 23-year-old Arsenal midfielder told John Hartson forBBC's Football Focus: 'My sporting hero was Graham Kavanagh. 

