'Coming through the ranks at Cardiff and going down to watch them a few times - he was the one player I looked up to.'

The current Carlisle manager made 16 appearances for the Republic of Ireland and enjoyed spells in the Premier League with Wigan and Middlesbrough before retiring in 2011.

Speaking to Wales legend Hartson for the quick-fire interview, Ramsey also revealed his toughest opponent to play against.

'Scott Parker,' the Arsenal midfielder added, 'he doesn't give you a moment's rest.' 

